isher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref>\n| 60\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|9|artist=Devin Townsend|album=Empath|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 10, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK2|23|date=20190405|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 6, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|169|artist=Devin Townsend|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 9, 2019}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Devin Townsend}}\n\n[[Category:Devin Townsend albums]]\n[[Category:2019 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Devin Townsend]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 album by Devin Townsend}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Empath\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Devin Townsend]]\n| cover      = Devin Townsend Empath cover.jpg \n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2019|3|29}}\n| recorded   = 2018\n| studio     = *Monnow Valley Studios, Rockfield, Wales, UK;\n*The Armoury Studios, The Farm, Devlab, and The Armory, Vancouver, Canada;\n*The Grid, Montreal, Canada.\n| genre      = [[Progressive metal]]\n| length     = 74:08\n| label      = *[[Inside Out Music|Inside Out]]\n*HevyDevy\n| producer   = Devin Townsend\n| prev_title = [[Transcendence (Devin Townsend Project album)|Transcendence]]\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = Devin Townsend solo\n | type       = Studio album\n | prev_title = [[Z\u00b2#Disc 2: Dark Matters|Dark Matters]]\n | prev_year  = 2014\n | title      = Empath\n | year       = 2019\n | next_title = \n | next_year  = \n}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = Empath\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Genesis\n | single1date = February 22, 2019\n | single2     = Evermore\n | single2date = March 15, 2019\n| single3     = Spirits Will Collide\n | single3date = March 29, 2019\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 84/100<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/empath/devin-townsend|title=Empath by Devin Townsend}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/empath-mw0003247719|title=Empath - Devin Townsend|date=2019|website=AllMusic}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Consequence of Sound]]''\n| rev2score = B+<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/03/album-review-devin-townsend-empath/|title=Devin Townsend\u2019s Glorious Sonically-Schizoid Journey Continues on Empath|date=March 26, 2019|website=Consequence of Sound}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n| rev3score = 8/10<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://exclaim.ca/music/article/devin_townsend-empath|title=Devin Townsend: Empath|date=March 29, 2019|website=Exclaim!}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''Metal Injection''\n| rev4score = 9.5/10<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://metalinjection.net/reviews/album-review-devin-townsend-empath/|title= Album Review: DEVIN TOWNSEND Empath}}</ref>\n| rev5 = [[MetalSucks]]\n| rev5score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metalsucks.net/2019/03/27/album-review-devin-townsend-achieves-enlightenment-with-empath/|title=Album Review: Devin Townsend Achieves Enlightenment with Empath|date=March 27, 2019|website=MetalSucks}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Sputnikmusic]]''\n| rev6score = 4.5/5<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/79313/Devin-Townsend-Empath/|title=Devin Townsend - Empath (album review ) &#124; Sputnikmusic|website=www.sputnikmusic.com}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Empath''''' is the eighteenth studio album by Canadian [[heavy metal music|metal]] musician [[Devin Townsend]], released on his own [[Record label|label]] HevyDevy Records on March 29, 2019. It is his first solo album since ''[[Z\u00b2 (album)#Disc 2: Dark Matters|Dark Matters]]'', which was a part of the 2014 double album ''[[Z\u00b2]]'', and his first release to act solely as a solo album since 2007's ''[[Ziltoid the Omniscient]]''.\n\n== Production ==\nOn January 31, 2018, Townsend announced on his Facebook page that he was taking a break from the Devin Townsend Project, which had been his main project since 2008, although 2014 saw the release of both ''[[Z\u00b2]]'', a dual release acting as both a solo album and a Devin Townsend Project album, and ''[[Casualties of Cool]]'', by Townsend's eponymous [[country rock]] duo; this made ''Empath'' Townsend's first release to act solely as a solo album since ''[[Ziltoid the Omniscient]]'' in 2007, and the first not to be a [[concept album]] since his 2006 [[Ambient music|ambient]] album ''[[The Hummer]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/dvntownsend/photos/a.175020189189978.40890.134347786590552/1999972140028098|title=Devin Townsend|website=facebook.com|access-date=2018-02-01|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180506015016/https://www.facebook.com/dvntownsend/photos/a.175020189189978.40890.134347786590552/1999972140028098|archivedate=May 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\nTownsend first mentioned ''Empath'' in a [[Twitter|tweet]] from January 1, 2017.<ref>{{citeweb |url=https://twitter.com/dvntownsend/status/815745344755511296 |title=Seems like a bunch of ideas want to be together... I think I'll call whatever this ends up being 'Empath' |work=Twitter |last=Townsend |first=Devin |date=1 January 2017 |accessdate=28 January 2019}}</ref> Two years later, on January 15, 2019, Townsend officially announced the album, on which work had already been completed, with a March 29, 2019 release date.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/upcoming-releases/devin-towsend-announces-empath-release-date-announces-mini-docuseries|title=DEVIN TOWSEND Announces Empath Release Date, Announces Mini-Docuseries|date=2019-01-16|website=Metal Injection|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref>\n\nA statement on his official [[Facebook]] page stated about the origins of the album:\n\n{{Quote\n| bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n| quoted=true\n| quote  =On this album Devin has decided to see what would happen if all the styles that make up his current interests were finally represented in one place. To finally shake the fear of expectation, and just do what it is he was meant to do creatively, EMPATH, true to the name, is about allowing the audience a feeling for a variety of musical emotions. The musical dynamics represented on this single album are broad, challenging, and immense. To approach this sort of work with a long history of what makes heavy music \u2018heavy\u2019, allows this to be done with a type of power rarely heard.\"<ref name=\"EmpathFacebook\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/dvntownsend/videos/vb.134347786590552/360542761167495/?type=2&theater|title=DEVIN TOWNSEND announces new album 'Empath'|via=[[Facebook]]|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref><ref name=\"EmpathBlabber\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/devin-townsend-to-release-empath-album-in-march-details-revealed/|title=DEVIN TOWNSEND To Release 'Empath' Album In March; Details Revealed|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|access-date=2019-01-17}}</ref>\n| width  =50%\n| qalign =center\n| salign =center\n| align  =center\n}}\n\nIt was also described as \"A bold statement with massive production values and dynamic, uncompromised musicality. This is a statement about not only pursuing creative freedom in a conservative scene, but also trying to show that heavy music is truly a valid musical tool.\"<ref name=\"EmpathFacebook\"/> Guest performers include former [[Frank Zappa]] collaborators [[Mike Keneally]], [[Morgan \u00c5gren]] and [[Steve Vai]], as well as Samus Paulicelli from [[Decrepit Birth]], Anup Sastry, [[Chad Kroeger]], Townsend's regular collaborator [[Anneke van Giersbergen]], Ch\u00e9 Aimee Dorval (who had worked with Townsend on ''[[Casualties of Cool]]''), Elliot Desgagn\u00e9s from [[Beneath The Massacre]], and [[Ryan Dahle]].<ref name=\"EmpathFacebook\"/><ref name=\"EmpathBlabber\"/>\n\nA series of documentary videos detailing the making of ''Empath'' has been released on YouTube.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lZBcGuM_UpE|title=YouTube|via=YouTube|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref>\n\nOn February 22, 2019, the first single from the album, \"Genesis\", was released. A corresponding video was also debuted that complemented the song's intricate style.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wallofsoundau.com/2019/02/24/watch-devin-townsends-bullshit-good-video-for-genesis/|title=Watch Devin Townsend\u2019s bullshit good video for 'Genesis'|last=brownypaul|date=2019-02-23|website=Wall of Sound|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref> On March 15, 2019, a second single titled \"Evermore\" was released; an accompanying music video was made for the single, which features a 2D animated cat flying through space.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metalsucks.net/2019/03/15/devin-townsend-evermore/|title=Devin Townsend Releases Sweet N' Silly New Song + Video, \"Evermore\"|date=March 15, 2019|website=MetalSucks}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''Empath'' was released on March 29, 2019. Editions include a limited 2-CD digipak with a disc of bonus material, a [[gatefold]] 180g 2-LP vinyl + CD + LP booklet edition.<ref name=\"EmpathFacebook\"/><ref name=\"EmpathBlabber\"/>\n\n== Critical response ==\n''Wall of Sound'' gave the album a perfect score of 10/10, writing: \"Devin's need for deeper creative expression has resulted in one of the year's most memorable works\".<ref name=\"WOSreview\">{{Cite web|url=https://wallofsoundau.com/2019/03/18/devin-townsend-empath-album-review/|title=Devin Townsend \u2013 Empath (Album Review)|last=walladmin|date=2019-03-17|website=Wall of Sound|access-date=2019-03-18}}</ref>\n\n''Angry Metal Guy'' contributor GardensTale gave ''Empath'' a score of 4.0/5.0, calling it \"...the most Devin album Devin ever recorded.\" <ref name=\"AMGreview\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.angrymetalguy.com/devin-townsend-empath-review/|title=Devin Townsend \u2013 Empath (Album Review)|last=GardensTale|date=2019-03-26|website=Angry Metal Guy|access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref>\n\nMP3s and NPCs writer Terrance Pryor listed the album at number four on their Top Albums of 2019 list, stating, \"With Empath, Devin Townsend pushed himself to the limits in terms of production, and the end result is a 74-minute tidal wave of sound.\" \n<ref>{{cite web|last = Pryor| first = Terrance|url=https://mp3sandnpcs.com/home/the-top-10-albums-of-2019|title=The top 10 albums of 2019|publisher=MP3s and NPCs|accessdate= January 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing     = [[Devin Townsend]] unless otherwise noted\n| total_length    = 74:08\n\n| title1          = Castaway\n| length1         = 2:28\n\n| title2          = Genesis\n| length2         = 6:05\n\n| title3          = Spirits Will Collide\n| length3         = 4:39\n\n| title4          = Evermore\n| length4         = 5:30\n\n| title5          = Sprite\n| length5         = 6:37\n\n| title6          = Hear Me\n| length6         = 6:30\n\n| title7          = Why?\n| length7         = 4:59\n\n| title8          = Borderlands\n| length8         = 11:02\n\n| title9          = Requiem\n| length9         = 2:46\n\n| title10 = Singularity\"\n*<small>\"I. Adrift\"</small>\n*<small>\"II. I Am I\"</small>\n*<small>\"III. There Be Monsters\"</small>\n*<small>\"IV. Curious Gods\" (co-written by [[Mike Keneally]] and [[Morgan \u00c5gren]])</small>\n*<small>\"V. Silicon Scientists\"</small>\n*<small>\"VI. Here Comes the Sun!</small>\n| length10 = 23:33\n*<small>5:00</small>\n*<small>3:29</small>\n*<small>4:37</small>\n*<small>3:08</small>\n*<small>2:55</small>\n*<small>4:23</small>\n\n }}\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Disc 2: Tests of Manhood (Limited Edition only)\n| collapsed = yes\n| title1          = The Contrarian\n| note1           = demo version\n| length1         = 5:41\n\n| title2          = King\n| note2           = demo version\n| length2         = 5:29\n\n| title3          = The Waiting Kind\n| note3           = demo version\n| length3         = 3:54\n\n| title4          = Empath\n| note4           = demo version, co-written by Keneally\n| length4         = 5:11\n\n| title5      