{"title_page": "List of judges of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom", "text_new": "This is a list of [[judges of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] since its creation on 1 October 2009 upon the transfer to the [[Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] of the [[judicial functions of the House of Lords]].\n\nThe court comprises a President, a Deputy President and 10 (puisne) Justices, for a total of 12 judges, of which \u2014 by convention \u2014 nine are from England and Wales, two from Scotland, and one from Northern Ireland. At the court's creation, 10 judges were appointed from the House of Lords, and one was appointed directly to it. The remaining initial vacancy was filled by [[John Dyson, Lord Dyson|Lord Dyson]] six months later. One of the original judges remains on the court.\n\n==List of judges of the Supreme Court==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!#\n! Served from !! Name !! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous judicial office !! Served until \n!Tenure length!! Replacing !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1\n| {{dts|1 October 2009}} || {{sortname|Lord|Phillips of Worth Maltravers|Nick Phillips, Baron Phillips of Worth Matravers}}||<small>[[Lords of Appeal in Ordinary#Senior and Second Senior Law Lord|Senior Lord of Appeal in Ordinary]] (2008\u201309)<br />[[Lord Chief Justice of England and Wales]] (2005\u201308)<br />[[Master of the Rolls]] (2000\u201305)<br />[[Lord of Appeal in Ordinary]] (1999\u20132000)</small> || {{dts|30 September 2012}} \n|{{age in years and days|2009|10|1|2012|09|30|sep=and|duration=on}}||  || [[President of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom|President]] 2009\u201312\n|-\n|2\n| {{dts|1 October 2009}} || {{sortname|Lord|Hope of Craighead|David Hope, Baron Hope of Craighead}}||<small>[[Lords of Appeal in Ordinary#Senior and Second Senior Law Lord|Second Senior Lord of Appeal in Ordinary]] (2009)<br /> [[Lord of Appeal in Ordinary]] (1996\u20132009)<br />[[Lord President of the Court of Session]] (1989\u201396)</sma