13|sep=and|duration=on}}\n|{{sortname|Baroness|Hale of Richmond|Brenda Hale, Baroness Hale of Richmond}}\n|\n|-\n|28\n|21 April 2020\n|[[George Leggatt|'''Lord Leggatt''']]\n|[[Lord Justice of Appeal|<small>Lord Justice of Appeal</small>]] <small>(2018\u20132020)</small><br><small>[[High Court judge (England and Wales)|Justice of the High Court]], [[Queen's Bench Division|QBD]] (2012\u20132018)</small>\n|''Incumbent''\n|{{age in years and days|2020|4|21|sep=and|duration=on}}\n|{{sortname|Lord|Carnwath of Notting Hill|Robert Carnwath, Lord Carnwath of Notting Hill}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Lords of Appeal in Ordinary]]\n*[[Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Constitutional Reform Act 2005]]\n*[[Courts of the United Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Supreme Court of the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of judges in the United Kingdom| Judges of the Supreme Court]]\n[[Category:Judges of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom| List]]\n[[Category:Lists of Supreme Court Justices|United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "This is a list of [[judges of the Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] since its creation on 1 October 2009 upon the transfer to the [[Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]] of the [[judicial functions of the House of Lords]].\n\nThe court comprises a President, a Deputy President and 10 (puisne) Justices, for a total of 12 judges, of which \u2014 by convention \u2014 nine are from England and Wales, two from Scotland, and one from Northern Ireland. At the court's creation, 10 judges were appointed from the House of Lords, and one was appointed directly to it. The remaining initial vacancy was filled by [[John Dyson, Lord Dyson|Lord Dyson]] six months later. One of the original judges remains on the court.\n\n==List of judges of the Supreme Court==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!#\n! Served from !! Name !! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous judicial office !! Served until \n!Tenure length!! Replacing !! class=\"unsortable\"