ars and days|2009|10|1|2011|05|07|sep=and|duration=on}}||  || Acting justice until July 2011<ref>{{cite web|title=Former Justices|url=http://www.supremecourt.uk/about/former-justices.html|publisher=[[Supreme Court of the United Kingdom]]|accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|11\n| {{dts|1 October 2009}} || '''{{sortname|The Lord|Kerr of Tonaghmore|Brian Kerr, Baron Kerr of Tonaghmore}}''' || <small>[[Lord of Appeal in Ordinary]] (2009)<br />[[Lord Chief Justice of Northern Ireland]] (2004\u201309)</small> || ''Incumbent'' \n|{{age in years and days|2009|10|1|sep=and|duration=on}}||  || \n|-\n|12\n| {{dts|13 April 2010}}||{{sortname|Lord|Dyson|John Dyson, Lord Dyson}}||<small>[[Master of the Rolls|Deputy Head of Civil Justice]] (2003\u201306)<br />[[Lord Justice of Appeal]] (2001\u201310)</small>||{{dts|1 October 2012}}\n|{{age in years and days|2010|04|13|2012|10|01|sep=and|duration=on}}||  || First non-life peer appointed to the Court<br />Stood down to become [[Master of the Rolls]]\n|-\n|13\n| {{dts|26 May 2011}} || '''{{sortname|Lord|Wilson of Culworth|Nicholas Wilson, Lord Wilson of Culworth}}''' || <small>[[Lord Justice of Appeal]] (2005\u201311)</small> || ''Incumbent'' \n|{{age in years and days|2011|05|26|sep=and|duration=on}}||{{sortname|The Lord|Saville of Newdigate|Mark Saville, Baron Saville of Newdigate}} || \n|-\n|14\n| {{dts|11 January 2012}} || {{sortname|Lord|Sumption|Jonathan Sumption, Lord Sumption}}||<small>None ''([[Queen's Counsel]] (1986\u20132012))''</small> || 9 December 2018 \n|{{age in years and days|2012|01|11|2018|12|09|sep=and|duration=on}}||{{sortname|The Lord|Collins of Mapesbury|Lawrence Collins, Baron Collins of Mapesbury}} || \n|-\n|15\n| {{dts|6 February 2012}} || '''{{sortname|Lord|Reed|Robert Reed, Lord Reed}}''' || <small>[[Senator of the College of Justice]] (1998\u20132012)</small> || ''Incumbent'' \n|{{age in years and days|2012|02|06|sep=and|duration=on}}||{{sortname|The Lord|Rodger of Earlsferry|Alan Rodger, Baron Rodger